TextEng: Goodbye.
Me have questions to ask you.
Why you say that?
<StartCheck>[Lie]</Start> Me seen lots with job collecting taxes.
I see lots in me adventures.
I have some questions to ask you.
Me need job.
Me need find stuff.
You hear strange stuff lately?
I am looking for work.
I need directions.
That's it. Goodbye.
Me want ask different thing.
I want to ask you something else.
Where me get healed?
Where me buy good stuff?
Where can I get healed?
Where can I get some equipment?
Path to destruction?
Have you heard anything unusual lately?
Text: 최근에 이상한 일 들은 거 있어요?

TextEng: Anything else?
Why do you say that?
<StartCheck>[Lie]</Start> As a tax collector I get to visit with a variety of people.
Sorry, me mistake. Me ask you some questions.
Text: 미안해, 나 실수했어. 나 질문 좀 할게.

TextEng: You be working for cult if you no give gold to help hunt them.
Text: 너 사교 일해 금화 안 주면 사교 위해 일하는 거야.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Lie]</Start> Me get gold to help Lady Aribeth hunt cult.
Text: <StartCheck>[거짓말]</Start> 나 금화 모아 아리베스 경 사교 잡는 거 도와.

TextEng: Sorry, nevermind. I want to ask you some questions.
Text: 미안해요, 잊어주세요. 질문 좀 하고 싶어요.

TextEng: Only someone who is in league with the cult we are hunting would refuse to give gold to help.
Text: 우리가 쫓는 사교와 한패인 사람만이 도움을 위한 금화를 거부할 거예요.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Lie]</Start> I work for Lady Aribeth, and I am collecting gold to help hunt down the cult that started the plague in Neverwinter.
Text: <StartCheck>[거짓말]</Start> 저는 아리베스 경을 위해 일하고, 네버윈터에 역병을 퍼뜨린 사교를 잡기 위한 금화를 모으고 있습니다.

TextEng: I have seen a lot in my adventures.
